  "prompt": "Any suggested cellphone units to make me active on messanger all the time using only my data?",
  "response": "If you're looking for a smartphone that allows you to stay active on Messenger using your data, you'll want a device with good connectivity, battery life, and performance. Here are some suggestions across various price ranges:\n\n### Budget Options\n1. **Moto G Power** \n   - Known for its excellent battery life, which can keep you active on Messenger all day.\n   - Offers decent performance for everyday tasks.\n\n2. **Samsung Galaxy A14 5G**\n   - Provides 5G connectivity, enhancing data speed and stability.\n   - Long-lasting battery and reliable performance.\n\n### Mid-Range Options\n1. **Google Pixel 6a**\n   - Offers clean Android experience with regular updates.\n   - Good camera and battery life, with efficient performance.\n\n2. **Samsung Galaxy A54 5G**\n   - Strong performance with good battery life.\n   - Offers 5G connectivity for faster data access.\n\n### Premium Options\n1. **Apple iPhone 14**\n   - Reliable performance and seamless integration with Messenger.\n   - Excellent battery life, display, and software optimization.\n\n2. **Samsung Galaxy S23**\n   - Top-tier performance, 5G connectivity, and a robust ecosystem.\n   - High-quality display and long battery life to stay connected all day.\n\n### Key Considerations\n- **Battery Life**: Crucial for staying active on Messenger without frequent recharging.\n- **Data Speed**: 5G-capable phones can provide better data performance.\n- **Performance**: Ensure the phone has enough processing power and memory for smooth multitasking.\n- **Operating System**: Choose based on preference for Android or iOS, as both support Messenger effectively.\n\nMake sure to also consider local availability and carrier compatibility to ensure the best experience with your chosen device.",
